---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import SectionLabel from '../../components/SectionLabel.astro';
---

<Base
  title="CalmAir Privacy Policy"
  description="CalmAir's privacy policy: the app collects no data, makes no network calls, and everything stays on your device."
>
  <section>
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-page px-8 py-section">
      <SectionLabel label="calmair · privacy policy" />
      <h1 class="mt-6 text-page-h1 text-text-primary max-w-prose">
        CalmAir collects nothing.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-card-body text-text-secondary max-w-prose">
        Last updated: July 2026
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="mx-auto max-w-page px-8 section-divider"></div>

  <section>
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-page px-8 py-section max-w-prose space-y-8">
      <div>
        <h2 class="mono-label">Data collection</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-card-body text-text-secondary">
          CalmAir makes no network calls of any kind. There are no accounts, no sign-in, no
          analytics SDKs, and no advertising identifiers. Every reading the app produces - motion
          data, barometer data, flight history, your appearance preferences - is generated and
          stored entirely on your device, and never transmitted anywhere. Apple's own App Privacy
          label for CalmAir reads "Data Not Collected," because none is.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mono-label">Sensors</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-card-body text-text-secondary">
          CalmAir uses your iPhone's motion sensor and barometer, with your permission, only
          while a flight session is active. This data is processed on-device to classify
          turbulence and estimate flight phase, then discarded or reduced to small per-minute
          summaries stored locally. Raw sensor data is never saved and never leaves your phone.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mono-label">Storage</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-card-body text-text-secondary">
          Flight history, settings, and purchase status are stored locally on your device using
          standard iOS storage (including the Keychain for purchase status). Deleting the app
          deletes this data. There is no cloud backup, no server, and no way for anyone -
          including the developer - to access it remotely.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mono-label">Purchases</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-card-body text-text-secondary">
          CalmAir's lifetime unlock is processed entirely through Apple's In-App Purchase system.
          Payment details are handled by Apple and never seen by CalmAir or its developer.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mono-label">Children</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-card-body text-text-secondary">
          CalmAir does not knowingly collect information from anyone, including children, because
          it does not collect information from anyone.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mono-label">Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-card-body text-text-secondary">
          If this policy ever changes, the update will be posted on this page with a new "last
          updated" date above.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mono-label">Contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-card-body text-text-secondary">
          Questions about this policy: <a href="mailto:stewart@stewart-burton.com" class="text-accent hover:underline">stewart@stewart-burton.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
